        <p>Music is an art form and cultural activity whose medium is sound organized
                in time. General definitions of music include common elements such as
                 pitch (which governs melody and harmony), rhythm (and its associated
                  concepts tempo, meter, and articulation), dynamics (loudness and softness),
                   and the sonic qualities of timbre and texture (which are sometimes termed
                    the "color" of a musical sound). Different styles or types of music may
                     emphasize, de-emphasize or omit some of these elements.
                      Music is performed with a vast range of instruments and vocal techniques
                       ranging from singing to rapping; there are solely instrumental pieces,
                        solely vocal pieces (such as songs without instrumental accompaniment)
                         and pieces that combine singing and instruments. </p>
